{
  "$schema": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/code-yeongyu/oh-my-openagent/dev/assets/oh-my-opencode.schema.json",

  // ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
  // Model routing policy
  // ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
  //
  // Tier policy:
  //   tier1 = long-horizon / hardest agentic work
  //   tier2 = strong balanced workhorse
  //   fast  = low-latency / high-volume checks
  //   free  = OpenCode Zen free + OpenRouter free last-resort continuity
  //
  // Distribution goal:
  // - spread primaries across providers to avoid hitting one provider's short limit
  // - keep cross-provider fallbacks semantically close
  // - final fallback chain includes OpenCode Zen free models and OpenRouter free models
  //
  // Core provider set:
  //   1. anthropic (direct)
  //   2. openai (direct)
  //   3. google (direct)
  //   4. minimax (direct)
  //   5. opencode-go
  //   6. opencode zen
  //   7. openrouter (ONLY free models)
  //
  // NEVER use openrouter/anthropic/*, openrouter/openai/* — paid via middleman.
  // Google exception: avoid Gemini as primary for long-running / high-fanout phases.
  // Use Gemini primarily for one-shot tasks where it is especially strong: writing and analysis.
  // See: docs/guides/pipeline-models/ for full policy.

  // ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
  // Sisyphus orchestrator
  // ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
  "agents": {
    "sisyphus": {
      "model": "opencode-go/glm-5",
      "variant": "max",
      "fallback_models": [
        "anthropic/claude-opus-4-6",                   // strongest architect-like fallback
        "openai/gpt-5.4",                              // strongest direct fallback
        "minimax/MiniMax-M2.7",                        // direct alt
        "opencode/big-pickle",                         // zen fallback
        "google/gemini-3.1-pro-preview",               // reserve only
        "openrouter/free"                              // last-resort free continuity
      ],
      "prompt_append": "## OpenSpec Pipeline Orchestration\n\nYou orchestrate the AI Community Platform pipeline.\n\n### Context routing\nYOU are the only one who reads handoff.md. Subagents do NOT read it.\n- Before each delegation: read handoff.md, extract relevant context\n- Pass context in the delegation prompt CONTEXT section\n- Tell each agent: \"Append results to handoff.md (your section only)\"\n- Between phases: re-read handoff.md to see what agents wrote\nException: s-summarizer reads handoff.md (its job is to summarize everything).\n\n### Pipeline phases\n\n**Phase 1 — Spec** (SKIP if tasks.md exists):\n- delegate_task(agent='s-architect', category='spec-writing')\n- Optionally delegate Explore in parallel for codebase research\n\n**Phase 2 — Implement:**\n- delegate_task(agent='s-coder', category='deep')\n\n**Phase 3 — Improvement pass:**\n- delegate_task(agent='s-reviewer', category='code-review')\n- Reviewer may refactor for SOLID, DRY, KISS, clean code, and safe stack-appropriate patterns\n\n**Phase 4 — Quality (PARALLEL):**\n- delegate_task(agent='s-validator', category='quick', run_in_background=true)\n- delegate_task(agent='s-tester', category='testing', run_in_background=true)\n- Wait for BOTH. Re-read handoff.md.\n- s-tester MUST check CUJ matrix (docs/agent-requirements/e2e-cuj-matrix.md) for UI changes and write E2E tests if missing\n\n**Phase 4b — E2E (OPTIONAL, if UI was changed):**\n- ONLY if tester wrote E2E tests or change touches admin UI\n- delegate_task(agent='s-tester', category='testing') with E2E focus\n- Task: run `make e2e-prepare && make e2e` if Docker is available\n- If Docker unavailable: SKIP with note in handoff\n\n**Phase 5 — Audit loop (ONLY if is_agent_task, max 3 iterations):**\n- delegate_task(agent='s-auditor', category='review') → read-only, writes report\n- Auditor checks E2E Coverage (E) section — missing CUJ = WARN (non-blocking)\n- If FAIL: generate fix tasks, delegate_task(agent='s-coder', category='deep') → delegate_task(agent='s-reviewer', category='code-review') → re-audit\n- If PASS or WARN on re-audit: proceed\n- After max 3 iterations: document remaining issues, let human decide\n\n**Phase 5b — Security review (OPTIONAL, if security-sensitive changes):**\n- ONLY if change touches auth, session, access control, input handling, file ops, or external HTTP calls\n- delegate_task(agent='s-security-review', category='security-review') → read-only, writes report\n- Advisory: WARN findings do not block. CRITICAL findings flagged for human review.\n- If CRITICAL found: note in handoff, optionally delegate fix to s-coder\n\n**Phase 6 — Documentation:**\n- delegate_task(agent='s-documenter', category='writing')\n\n**Phase 6b — Translation (OPTIONAL, if i18n/docs changed):**\n- ONLY if change touches translations/*.yaml, *.html.twig with trans filter, or docs/**/*.md\n- delegate_task(agent='s-translater', category='translation')\n- Translater syncs missing translations and mirrors docs between UA/EN\n\n**Phase 7 — Summarize:**\n- delegate_task(agent='s-summarizer', category='analysis')\n- Summarizer MUST write `builder/tasks/summary/<timestamp>-<slug>.md` on both success and failure\n\n### Resilience rules\n\n1. **Subagent failure**: if a delegate_task fails or returns an error, update handoff.md with status=failed and reason, then CONTINUE to the next phase. Never get stuck waiting.\n2. **Parallel timeout**: if one parallel task finishes but the other is still running, wait max ~2 minutes. If still not done, mark it as status=timeout in handoff and proceed.\n3. **Always finalize**: Phase 6 (summarizer) MUST run even if earlier phases failed. Write summary with whatever results exist.\n4. **Handoff is truth**: after EVERY phase, update handoff.md immediately. If you crash, the next /finish run can resume from handoff state.\n5. **Budget awareness**: you have limited tokens. If you've completed 4+ phases, prioritize summarizer over remaining optional phases.\n\n### Shortcuts\n- 'ulw' / 'ultrawork' → full pipeline (phases 1-6)\n- '/implement <change-id>' → phases 2-6\n- '/validate' → phase 4 only\n- '/audit' → phase 5 only\n- '/finish' → resume from handoff.md state\n\n### Delegation template\nEvery delegation MUST follow:\n```\nTASK: <atomic goal>\nEXPECTED OUTCOME: <deliverables>\nREQUIRED TOOLS: <whitelist>\nMUST DO:\n  - <requirements>\n  - Append results to .opencode/pipeline/handoff.md (your section only)\nMUST NOT DO:\n  - Do NOT read handoff.md\n  - <forbidden actions>\nCONTEXT:\n  - Apps: <from handoff.md>\n  - Changed files: <from previous phase>\n  - Spec: <path>\n```"
    },

    // ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
    // Subagent model overrides + fallbacks
    // ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
    //
    // Rule: every agent has 6 providers represented.
    // Primaries are intentionally spread across providers to reduce rate-limit coupling.

    "s-architect": {
      "model": "anthropic/claude-opus-4-6",
      "fallback_models": [
        "openai/gpt-5.4",                              // strongest direct fallback
        "opencode-go/glm-5",                           // strongest long-horizon fallback
        "minimax/MiniMax-M2.7",                        // tier1 direct alt
        "google/gemini-3.1-pro-preview",               // strong one-shot reasoning alt
        "opencode/big-pickle",                         // tier1 zen
        "openrouter/free"                              // free reasoning backup
      ]
    },

    "s-coder": {
      "model": "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6",
      "fallback_models": [
        "minimax/MiniMax-M2.7",                        // strong coding workhorse
        "openai/gpt-5.3-codex",                        // strongest coding fallback
        "opencode-go/glm-5",                           // tier1 coding alt
        "google/gemini-3.1-pro-preview",               // reserve only
        "opencode/big-pickle",                         // tier1 zen
        "openrouter/qwen/qwen3-coder:free"             // free coding backup
      ]
    },

    "s-reviewer": {
      "model": "minimax/MiniMax-M2.7",
      "fallback_models": [
        "openai/gpt-5.4",                              // strongest review fallback
        "opencode-go/glm-5",                           // strong structural alt
        "opencode/big-pickle",                         // zen fallback
        "google/gemini-3.1-pro-preview",               // reserve only
        "openrouter/qwen/qwen3-coder:free"             // free code-quality backup
      ]
    },

    "s-validator": {
      "model": "minimax/MiniMax-M2.5-highspeed",
      "fallback_models": [
        "openai/gpt-5.2",                              // fast enough and locally available
        "opencode-go/kimi-k2.5",                       // balanced opencode-go
        "opencode/minimax-m2.5-free",                  // zen free/cheap fallback
        "google/gemini-3.1-flash-lite-preview",        // reserve only
        "openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-r1-0528-qwen3-8b:free"  // free fast backup
      ]
    },

    "s-tester": {
      "model": "opencode-go/kimi-k2.5",
      "fallback_models": [
        "openai/gpt-5.3-codex",                        // tier1 coding alt
        "minimax/MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed",              // coding/testing alt
        "opencode/big-pickle",                         // zen fallback
        "google/gemini-3.1-pro-preview",               // reserve only
        "openrouter/qwen/qwen3-coder:free"             // free coding backup
      ]
    },

    "s-auditor": {
      "model": "anthropic/claude-opus-4-6",
      "fallback_models": [
        "openai/gpt-5.4",                              // strongest direct alt
        "opencode-go/glm-5",                           // long-horizon audit alt
        "minimax/MiniMax-M2.7",                        // tier1 direct alt
        "opencode/big-pickle",                         // tier1 zen
        "google/gemini-3.1-pro-preview",               // reserve only
        "openrouter/free"                              // free reasoning backup
      ]
    },

    "s-documenter": {
      "model": "openai/gpt-5.4",
      "fallback_models": [
        "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6",                 // strong writing fallback
        "google/gemini-3-flash-preview",               // one-shot writing alt
        "minimax/MiniMax-M2.5",                        // tier2 direct alt
        "opencode-go/kimi-k2.5",                       // tier2 opencode-go
        "opencode/big-pickle",                         // zen writing fallback
        "openrouter/free"                              // free continuity
      ]
    },

    "s-summarizer": {
      "model": "openai/gpt-5.4",
      "fallback_models": [
        "anthropic/claude-opus-4-6",                   // strongest analysis fallback
        "google/gemini-3.1-pro-preview",               // one-shot analysis alt
        "minimax/MiniMax-M2.7",                        // strong reasoning alt
        "opencode-go/glm-5",                           // long-horizon analysis alt
        "opencode/big-pickle",                         // zen analysis fallback
        "openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-r1-0528:free"    // free reasoning continuity
      ]
    },

    "s-translater": {
      "model": "google/gemini-3.1-pro-preview",
      "fallback_models": [
        "openai/gpt-5.4",                              // strong multilingual writing
        "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6",                 // balanced writing fallback
        "minimax/MiniMax-M2.5",                        // tier2 direct alt
        "opencode-go/kimi-k2.5",                       // tier2 opencode-go
        "opencode/big-pickle",                         // zen writing fallback
        "openrouter/free"                              // free continuity
      ]
    },

    "s-security-review": {
      "model": "anthropic/claude-opus-4-6",
      "fallback_models": [
        "openai/gpt-5.4",                              // strongest direct alt
        "opencode-go/glm-5",                           // long-horizon analysis alt
        "minimax/MiniMax-M2.7",                        // tier1 direct alt
        "opencode/big-pickle",                         // tier1 zen
        "google/gemini-3.1-pro-preview",               // reserve only
        "openrouter/free"                              // free reasoning backup
      ]
    }
  },

  // ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
  // Custom categories for pipeline delegation
  // ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  "categories": {
    "spec-writing": {
      "model": "anthropic/claude-opus-4-6",
      "fallback_models": [
        "openai/gpt-5.4",
        "opencode-go/glm-5",
        "minimax/MiniMax-M2.7",
        "google/gemini-3.1-pro-preview",
        "opencode/big-pickle",
        "openrouter/free"
      ],
      "prompt_append": "Load the openspec skill. Follow OpenSpec conventions."
    },
    "deep": {
      "model": "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6",
      "fallback_models": [
        "minimax/MiniMax-M2.7",
        "openai/gpt-5.3-codex",
        "opencode-go/glm-5",
        "google/gemini-3.1-pro-preview",
        "opencode/big-pickle",
        "openrouter/qwen/qwen3-coder:free"
      ],
      "prompt_append": "Load the coding skill for per-app targets."
    },
    "code-review": {
      "model": "minimax/MiniMax-M2.7",
      "fallback_models": [
        "openai/gpt-5.4",
        "opencode-go/glm-5",
        "opencode/big-pickle",
        "google/gemini-3.1-pro-preview",
        "openrouter/qwen/qwen3-coder:free"
      ],
      "prompt_append": "Review and improve code for SOLID, DRY, KISS, clean code, and stack-appropriate patterns. Apply only safe, low-regression improvements."
    },
    "testing": {
      "model": "opencode-go/kimi-k2.5",
      "fallback_models": [
        "openai/gpt-5.3-codex",
        "minimax/MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed",
        "opencode/big-pickle",
        "google/gemini-3.1-pro-preview",
        "openrouter/qwen/qwen3-coder:free"
      ],
      "prompt_append": "Load the testing skill. Iterate until all green."
    },
    "review": {
      "model": "anthropic/claude-opus-4-6",
      "fallback_models": [
        "openai/gpt-5.4",
        "opencode-go/glm-5",
        "minimax/MiniMax-M2.7",
        "opencode/big-pickle",
        "google/gemini-3.1-pro-preview",
        "openrouter/free"
      ],
      "tools": { "edit": "deny", "write": "deny" },
      "prompt_append": "Load the auditing skill. Read-only — do NOT modify files."
    },
    "writing": {
      "model": "openai/gpt-5.4",
      "fallback_models": [
        "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6",
        "google/gemini-3-flash-preview",
        "minimax/MiniMax-M2.5",
        "opencode-go/kimi-k2.5",
        "opencode/big-pickle",
        "openrouter/free"
      ],
      "prompt_append": "Load the documentation skill."
    },
    "quick": {
      "model": "minimax/MiniMax-M2.5-highspeed",
      "fallback_models": [
        "openai/gpt-5.2",
        "opencode-go/kimi-k2.5",
        "opencode/minimax-m2.5-free",
        "google/gemini-3.1-flash-lite-preview",
        "openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-r1-0528-qwen3-8b:free"
      ]
    },
    "analysis": {
      "model": "openai/gpt-5.4",
      "fallback_models": [
        "anthropic/claude-opus-4-6",
        "google/gemini-3.1-pro-preview",
        "minimax/MiniMax-M2.7",
        "opencode-go/glm-5",
        "opencode/big-pickle",
        "openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-r1-0528-qwen3-8b:free"
      ]
    },
    "translation": {
      "model": "google/gemini-3.1-pro-preview",
      "fallback_models": [
        "openai/gpt-5.4",
        "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6",
        "minimax/MiniMax-M2.5",
        "opencode-go/kimi-k2.5",
        "opencode/big-pickle",
        "openrouter/free"
      ],
      "prompt_append": "Load the translater skill. Translate by context, maintain term consistency."
    },
    "security-review": {
      "model": "anthropic/claude-opus-4-6",
      "fallback_models": [
        "openai/gpt-5.4",
        "opencode-go/glm-5",
        "minimax/MiniMax-M2.7",
        "opencode/big-pickle",
        "google/gemini-3.1-pro-preview",
        "openrouter/free"
      ],
      "tools": { "edit": "deny", "write": "deny" },
      "prompt_append": "Load the security-review skill. Read-only — do NOT modify files."
    }
  },

  // ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
  // Background concurrency
  // ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  "background_task": {
    "defaultConcurrency": 5,
    "staleTimeoutMs": 300000,
    "providerConcurrency": {
      "opencode-go": 3,
      "anthropic": 3,
      "openai": 4,
      "google": 2,
      "minimax": 4,
      "opencode": 3,
      "openrouter": 6
    },
    "modelConcurrency": {
      "anthropic/claude-opus-4-6": 2,
      "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6": 3,
      "openai/gpt-5.4": 2,
      "minimax/MiniMax-M2.7": 3,
      "opencode-go/glm-5": 3,
      "minimax/MiniMax-M2.5-highspeed": 4
    }
  },

  // ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
  // Tmux live monitoring
  // ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  "tmux": {
    "enabled": true,
    "layout": "main-vertical",
    "main_pane_size": 55
  },

  // ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
  // Runtime fallback on rate limits
  // ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  "model_fallback": true
}
